WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:19.920
Cambridge English readers, starter level, The Black Pearls by Richard McCandrew, published

00:19.920 --> 00:40.360
by Cambridge University Press. This recording is copyright.

00:40.360 --> 00:43.840
The Black Pearls by Richard McCandrew

00:49.920 --> 00:59.920
Chapter 1 Who is Wolfgang Peters?

00:59.920 --> 01:11.920
This is the man, says Janet Hunter, and she puts a photo on the table. Janet Hunter is a police inspector from New Zealand.

01:11.920 --> 01:19.920
She's in the police station on Rauratonga, one of the Cook Islands in the Pacific Ocean.

01:19.920 --> 01:21.920
What's his name?

01:21.920 --> 01:30.920
asks to Nui Epatty. Epatty is an inspector in the Cook Islands police.

01:30.920 --> 01:40.920
His name is Wolfgang Peters, she answers. Some people call him the minute man.

01:40.920 --> 01:52.920
Why? Epatty asks. Because one minute he's there, and the next minute he's not, answers Hunter.

01:52.920 --> 01:55.920
Epatty smiles.

01:55.920 --> 02:04.920
And why do you want him? Epatty asks. He looks at the photo.

02:04.920 --> 02:15.920
He steals, answers Hunter. He takes things, often from museums. People tell him what they want.

02:15.920 --> 02:23.920
Then he steals for them, and he gets very good money for his work.

02:23.920 --> 02:28.920
What kind of things does he take? asks Epatty.

02:28.920 --> 02:37.920
Anything? answers Hunter. A Faberge egg from a museum in Virginia, in the United States.

02:37.920 --> 02:43.920
A Picasso painting from a museum in St. Petersburg, in Russia.

02:43.920 --> 02:50.920
And then this year, an old book from a museum in Auckland, in New Zealand.

02:50.920 --> 02:56.920
It's the only one in the world. That's why I'm after him.

02:56.920 --> 03:01.920
I see, says Epatty.

03:01.920 --> 03:10.920
Peters is very good, says Hunter. But I want him, and I'm going to get him.

03:11.920 --> 03:18.920
And he's coming here? To Rada Tonga? asks Epatty.

03:18.920 --> 03:27.920
Yes, says Hunter. We, the New Zealand police, think he's going to steal something here.

03:27.920 --> 03:31.920
Ah, says Epatty.

03:31.920 --> 03:36.920
Then I know what, I think.

03:36.920 --> 03:43.920
Epatty takes down a book and opens it. Hunter watches him.

03:43.920 --> 03:50.920
Many Cook Islanders are big people. Epatty is big.

03:50.920 --> 04:00.920
He gives Hunter the book. It's open at a photo of a beautiful necklace of black pearls.

04:00.920 --> 04:06.920
That is the Manihiki necklace, says Epatty.

04:06.920 --> 04:10.920
It's from the island of Manihiki.

04:10.920 --> 04:19.920
Manihiki is a thousand kilometers from Rada Tonga, but it's one of the Cook Islands too.

04:19.920 --> 04:22.920
Hunter looks at the necklace.

04:23.920 --> 04:27.920
It's beautiful, she says.

04:27.920 --> 04:38.920
Yes, says Epatty. And over a hundred years old, those are black pearls.

04:38.920 --> 04:47.920
They're not easy to find. You only get them in Tahiti and here in the Cook Islands.

04:47.920 --> 04:50.920
Hunter looks up at Epatty.

04:50.920 --> 04:57.920
The necklace is in the museum here, says Epatty.

04:57.920 --> 05:02.920
People from all over the world come to see it.

05:02.920 --> 05:06.920
He takes the photo of Peters from the table.

05:06.920 --> 05:10.920
Can I have this photo? He asks.

05:10.920 --> 05:16.920
Of course, answers Hunter. Then she says,

05:16.920 --> 05:21.920
Peters is coming here this morning on a plane from Tahiti.

05:21.920 --> 05:28.920
I want to watch him and try and get him. But is that okay with you?

05:28.920 --> 05:32.920
After all, this is your island.

05:32.920 --> 05:35.920
That's okay, says Epatty.

05:35.920 --> 05:42.920
Do you want any help? We have some good people in the Cook Islands police.

05:42.920 --> 05:48.920
Thank you, says Hunter. But not now. I can call you.

05:48.920 --> 05:54.920
Of course, says Epatty. Call me by five o'clock.

05:54.920 --> 06:01.920
Okay, says Hunter. They go out of the police station.

06:01.920 --> 06:05.920
Which hotel are you in? Asks Epatty.

06:05.920 --> 06:09.920
The water side in? Answers Hunter.

06:09.920 --> 06:13.920
Good hotel, says Epatty.

06:13.920 --> 06:17.920
Is this your first time in the Cook Islands?

06:17.920 --> 06:23.920
Yes, says Hunter. It's very beautiful here.

06:23.920 --> 06:30.920
Well, thank you for your help, Inspector. I must get to the airport by eleven o'clock.

06:30.920 --> 06:40.920
Chapter Two. Watching Peters.

06:40.920 --> 06:45.920
A lot of people are waiting in front of the airport.

06:45.920 --> 06:50.920
What are all these people doing, thinks Hunter?

06:50.920 --> 06:55.920
She walks across and speaks to a Cook Islands woman.

06:55.920 --> 06:59.920
Why is everyone here? She asks.

06:59.920 --> 07:03.920
Kate Watson is coming, the woman answers.

07:03.920 --> 07:10.920
You know, the Kate Watson. She's in a lot of Hollywood films.

07:10.920 --> 07:15.920
Oh, her, says Hunter.

07:15.920 --> 07:19.920
Is she making a film here? She asks.

07:19.920 --> 07:26.920
Yes, but she's only on the island for two or three days.

07:26.920 --> 07:30.920
Hunter waits next to the woman for a minute or two.

07:30.920 --> 07:34.920
Then she goes to her car.

07:34.920 --> 07:41.920
At about eleven forty-five, Wolfgang Peters comes out of the airport.

07:41.920 --> 07:45.920
He's a short man with dark hair.

07:45.920 --> 07:49.920
Hunter watches from her car.

07:49.920 --> 07:53.920
Peters finds a taxi and gets in.

07:53.920 --> 08:00.920
The taxi drives away. Hunter drives behind it.

08:00.920 --> 08:07.920
After fifteen minutes, the taxi stops at the water side in,

08:07.920 --> 08:11.920
and Peters gets out with his bags.

08:11.920 --> 08:15.920
That's good, thinks Hunter.

08:15.920 --> 08:21.920
He's at this hotel too. It's going to be easy to watch him.

08:21.920 --> 08:27.920
She sits in her car across the street and waits.

08:27.920 --> 08:32.920
At one thirty, Peters comes out of the hotel.

08:32.920 --> 08:40.920
A taxi is waiting. Peters gets in and the taxi drives away.

08:40.920 --> 08:44.920
Hunter is behind them.

08:44.920 --> 08:49.920
Peters' taxi takes him to the museum.

08:49.920 --> 08:54.920
He gets out and walks into the museum.

08:54.920 --> 08:59.920
Hunter leaves her car and goes in too.

08:59.920 --> 09:02.920
The museum is small.

09:02.920 --> 09:07.920
There are a lot of interesting things from the Cook Islands

09:07.920 --> 09:11.920
and from Tahiti, Tonga and Fiji.

09:11.920 --> 09:17.920
Hunter looks at some old bags and jackets from the Cook Islands,

09:17.920 --> 09:21.920
but she watches Peters too.

09:21.920 --> 09:26.920
He's looking at the money he can necklace.

09:26.920 --> 09:30.920
After a minute or two, he looks across the room.

09:30.920 --> 09:36.920
Hunter turns and walks over to a boat from the time of Captain Cook.

09:36.920 --> 09:40.920
She doesn't want Peters to see her.

09:40.920 --> 09:43.920
Peters looks at the necklace again.

09:43.920 --> 09:47.920
Then he leaves the museum.

09:47.920 --> 09:50.920
Hunter waits five minutes.

09:50.920 --> 09:59.920
Then she too leaves and goes to the water side in.

10:00.920 --> 10:05.920
Chapter 3. At CJ's Cafe

10:05.920 --> 10:09.920
Peters is here, says Hunter.

10:09.920 --> 10:12.920
It's six o'clock in the evening.

10:12.920 --> 10:17.920
She's sitting with Tanui Ipati at CJ's Cafe.

10:17.920 --> 10:20.920
They're looking out over the water.

10:20.920 --> 10:25.920
And he is going to steal the money he can necklace.

10:26.920 --> 10:31.920
Well, says Ipati, we can stop him.

10:31.920 --> 10:36.920
I can get some police officers to watch the necklace all the time.

10:36.920 --> 10:41.920
Or we can try and get him with the necklace.

10:41.920 --> 10:46.920
I want to get him with the necklace, says Hunter.

10:46.920 --> 10:49.920
But it's not going to be easy.

10:49.920 --> 10:52.920
He is very good at his job.

10:53.920 --> 11:02.920
I can put some police officers in the museum, says Ipati, where Peters can't see them.

11:02.920 --> 11:10.920
You can, says Hunter, but they're not going to get him, asks Ipati.

11:10.920 --> 11:13.920
Hunter smiles.

11:13.920 --> 11:17.920
The police never do, she says.

11:17.920 --> 11:20.920
Well, says Ipati.

11:20.920 --> 11:23.920
He's at the water side in.

11:23.920 --> 11:27.920
We can look for the necklace in his room.

11:27.920 --> 11:32.920
You can try looking in his room too, says Hunter.

11:32.920 --> 11:36.920
But he never has the things with him.

11:36.920 --> 11:42.920
Virginia, St. Petersburg, Auckland, the police never find anything.

11:42.920 --> 11:46.920
But she stops and thinks.

11:46.920 --> 11:51.920
He has a plane ticket to Tahiti the day after tomorrow.

11:51.920 --> 11:55.920
And he's not going to leave the necklace here in Raritonga.

11:55.920 --> 11:59.920
No, Ipati says.

11:59.920 --> 12:02.920
Peters isn't working for a Cook Islander.

12:02.920 --> 12:05.920
No one here has that much money.

12:05.920 --> 12:09.920
Peters is going to have the necklace with him at the airport.

12:09.920 --> 12:12.920
We can get him there.

12:12.920 --> 12:16.920
And no police officers in the museum?

12:16.920 --> 12:18.920
Ask Hunter?

12:18.920 --> 12:22.920
No, says Ipati.

12:22.920 --> 12:27.920
Ipati and Hunter leave CJ's cafe.

12:27.920 --> 12:34.920
Across the street, a lot of people are waiting in front of the Itutaki restaurant.

12:34.920 --> 12:37.920
Some police officers are there too.

12:37.920 --> 12:42.920
A car drives up and two women get out.

12:42.920 --> 12:48.920
The first has long red hair and is very beautiful.

12:48.920 --> 12:52.920
Hunter knows her face from films and papers.

12:52.920 --> 12:57.920
People shout, Kate! Kate!

12:57.920 --> 12:59.920
How are you, Kate?

12:59.920 --> 13:03.920
Do you like Raritonga, Kate?

13:03.920 --> 13:06.920
The second woman has dark hair.

13:06.920 --> 13:08.920
She's beautiful too.

13:08.920 --> 13:11.920
Hunter looks at Ipati.

13:11.920 --> 13:15.920
Who's the woman with dark hair? She asks.

13:15.920 --> 13:20.920
Maria Gomez answers Ipati.

13:20.920 --> 13:23.920
She's in the Kate Watson film too.

13:23.920 --> 13:30.920
She's not famous now, but people say she's the next big thing.

13:30.920 --> 13:35.920
The women smile and go into the restaurant.

13:35.920 --> 13:38.920
Ipati looks at Hunter.

13:38.920 --> 13:44.920
Hollywood comes to Raritonga, he says, with a small smile.

13:44.920 --> 13:51.920
It's all work for me.

13:51.920 --> 13:54.920
Chapter 4

13:54.920 --> 13:58.920
Who takes the necklace?

13:58.920 --> 14:03.920
At 9 o'clock the next morning, the museum is opening.

14:03.920 --> 14:07.920
Hunter is sitting in her car.

14:07.920 --> 14:11.920
She's watching the front door of the museum.

14:11.920 --> 14:17.920
After five minutes, Ipati comes out and walks across to her.

14:17.920 --> 14:22.920
The people at the museum understand, says Ipati.

14:22.920 --> 14:28.920
They know about Peter's and they're not going to try and stop him.

14:28.920 --> 14:31.920
Okay, says Hunter.

14:31.920 --> 14:34.920
Well, says Ipati.

14:34.920 --> 14:36.920
I'm leaving.

14:36.920 --> 14:40.920
We don't want Peter's to see any police officers here.

14:40.920 --> 14:42.920
And I've got work to do.

14:42.920 --> 14:45.920
What are you going to do?

14:45.920 --> 14:51.920
I'm just going to wait here in the car for now and watch, says Hunter.

14:51.920 --> 14:53.920
Okay.

14:53.920 --> 14:57.920
Ipati gets in his car and drives away.

14:57.920 --> 15:01.920
People come and go in and out of the museum.

15:01.920 --> 15:12.920
Then, at about 1130, a taxi drives up and a woman with long dark hair gets out.

15:12.920 --> 15:15.920
She has a bag in one hand.

15:15.920 --> 15:21.920
She looks at Hunter's car and then walks into the museum fast.

15:21.920 --> 15:24.920
Hunter watches the woman.

15:24.920 --> 15:27.920
Something's wrong, she thinks.

15:27.920 --> 15:30.920
I don't think that's a woman.

15:30.920 --> 15:33.920
She gets out of her car fast.

15:33.920 --> 15:37.920
There's a noise from the museum and a lot of shouting.

15:37.920 --> 15:43.920
She runs to the museum, but people are running out with their hands over their faces.

15:43.920 --> 15:46.920
Hunter tries to get in, but she can't.

15:46.920 --> 15:48.920
She runs to the back door.

15:48.920 --> 15:50.920
It's open.

15:50.920 --> 15:53.920
Two people from the museum come out.

15:53.920 --> 15:56.920
The necklace shouts one.

15:56.920 --> 16:03.920
It's not there.

16:03.920 --> 16:05.920
Chapter 5.

16:05.920 --> 16:09.920
Peters knows nothing.

16:09.920 --> 16:13.920
The minute man says Ipati.

16:13.920 --> 16:16.920
Yes, says Hunter.

16:16.920 --> 16:20.920
There one minute knocked the next.

16:20.920 --> 16:24.920
Or this time, he's the minute woman.

16:24.920 --> 16:33.920
It's six o'clock in the evening and they're drinking coconut water at the water side in.

16:33.920 --> 16:35.920
What does Peters say?

16:35.920 --> 16:37.920
asks Hunter.

16:37.920 --> 16:40.920
Nothing answers Ipati.

16:40.920 --> 16:46.920
Three hours of questions this afternoon and no answers from him.

16:46.920 --> 16:51.920
He's not the woman at the museum, asks Hunter.

16:51.920 --> 16:55.920
Her mouth smiles, but not her eyes.

16:55.920 --> 16:59.920
He says not, says Ipati.

16:59.920 --> 17:02.920
Of course, says Hunter.

17:02.920 --> 17:05.920
And what about his room here?

17:05.920 --> 17:09.920
No necklace, says Ipati.

17:09.920 --> 17:13.920
No long dark hair, nothing.

17:13.920 --> 17:16.920
Then why is he in raretonga?

17:16.920 --> 17:18.920
asks Hunter.

17:18.920 --> 17:21.920
She smiles again.

17:21.920 --> 17:26.920
He says he's just enjoying our beautiful island, says Ipati.

17:26.920 --> 17:31.920
Lots of good food and friendly people.

17:31.920 --> 17:33.920
Where is he now?

17:33.920 --> 17:35.920
asks Hunter.

17:35.920 --> 17:40.920
Here, in the restaurant, eating and drinking.

17:40.920 --> 17:42.920
Ipati laughs.

17:42.920 --> 17:48.920
And this evening, there's some Cook Islands dancing at the hotel.

17:48.920 --> 17:55.920
He's going to watch that because he tells me he loves dancing.

17:55.920 --> 17:59.920
He's good, says Hunter.

17:59.920 --> 18:03.920
Very good, says Ipati.

18:03.920 --> 18:06.920
Ipati looks at Hunter.

18:06.920 --> 18:09.920
Do you like dancing?

18:09.920 --> 18:11.920
He asks.

18:11.920 --> 18:14.920
I do now, she answers.

18:14.920 --> 18:18.920
I want to watch Peters.

18:18.920 --> 18:24.920
At nine o'clock, Hunter leaves her room and goes down to the restaurant.

18:24.920 --> 18:28.920
She hears a lot of noise and shouting.

18:28.920 --> 18:30.920
Kate! Kate!

18:30.920 --> 18:32.920
Are you here for the dancing?

18:32.920 --> 18:36.920
Do you like Cook Islands dancing?

18:36.920 --> 18:40.920
Kate Watson comes into the hotel.

18:40.920 --> 18:43.920
Maria Gomez is with her.

18:43.920 --> 18:47.920
Hunter walks into the restaurant behind them.

18:47.920 --> 18:53.920
In the restaurant, Kate Watson and Maria Gomez sit at the front.

18:53.920 --> 18:56.920
Hunter looks for Peters.

18:56.920 --> 19:01.920
He is sitting behind Kate Watson.

19:01.920 --> 19:04.920
The dancing starts.

19:04.920 --> 19:10.920
Men, women, boys and girls, all with flowers in their hair.

19:10.920 --> 19:14.920
Beautiful dances to beautiful music.

19:14.920 --> 19:17.920
Everyone enjoys it.

19:17.920 --> 19:23.920
The dancing finishes at 10.30, and everyone gets up to leave.

19:23.920 --> 19:26.920
People go to the restaurant doors.

19:26.920 --> 19:30.920
Hunter waits and watches.

19:30.920 --> 19:33.920
Peters speaks to one or two people.

19:33.920 --> 19:36.920
Then he goes to the doors.

19:36.920 --> 19:39.920
Watson and Gomez are leaving too.

19:39.920 --> 19:43.920
Hunter can just see their heads.

19:43.920 --> 19:46.920
Peters is just in front of them.

19:46.920 --> 19:49.920
Kate Watson says something to him.

19:49.920 --> 19:54.920
He turns and smiles, but says nothing.

19:54.920 --> 19:57.920
People out on the street are shouting,

19:57.920 --> 20:00.920
Kate! Kate!

20:00.920 --> 20:03.920
Hunter watches Peters.

20:03.920 --> 20:06.920
He turns left to his room.

20:06.920 --> 20:18.920
Kate Watson and Maria Gomez go out of the hotel and get into a car.

20:18.920 --> 20:20.920
Chapter 6.

20:20.920 --> 20:23.920
At the airport.

20:23.920 --> 20:26.920
It's ten o'clock in the morning,

20:26.920 --> 20:30.920
and Hunter and Aparti are at the airport.

20:30.920 --> 20:33.920
They're watching people.

20:33.920 --> 20:36.920
Two planes are leaving this morning.

20:36.920 --> 20:41.920
One to Tahiti, one to Los Angeles.

20:41.920 --> 20:43.920
Across the room,

20:43.920 --> 20:47.920
Hunter sees Kate Watson and Maria Gomez.

20:47.920 --> 20:51.920
Someone behind them has their bags.

20:51.920 --> 20:54.920
There's a lot of noise.

20:54.920 --> 20:57.920
The women are late for their plane.

20:57.920 --> 21:00.920
An airport worker looks at their tickets,

21:00.920 --> 21:03.920
and then they run to the plane.

21:03.920 --> 21:06.920
After two or three minutes,

21:06.920 --> 21:09.920
Hunter and Aparti see Peters.

21:09.920 --> 21:12.920
They run over and stop him.

21:12.920 --> 21:15.920
Excuse me, Mr Peters.

21:15.920 --> 21:17.920
Says Aparti.

21:17.920 --> 21:21.920
Can I look in your bags, please?

21:21.920 --> 21:25.920
Of course, says Peters.

21:25.920 --> 21:30.920
Aparti takes the two bags from Peters.

21:30.920 --> 21:33.920
He starts looking in one bag.

21:33.920 --> 21:40.920
Hunter takes out Peters' computer and opens it.

21:40.920 --> 21:46.920
I don't have that necklace, you know, says Peters to Aparti.

21:46.920 --> 21:50.920
I know nothing about it.

21:50.920 --> 21:54.920
Aparti finishes looking in Peters' bag.

21:54.920 --> 21:58.920
Nothing here, he says to Hunter.

21:58.920 --> 22:01.920
Then he looks at Peters.

22:01.920 --> 22:06.920
Okay, he says, put your arms up.

22:06.920 --> 22:12.920
He tries Peters jacket, his trousers, everywhere.

22:12.920 --> 22:15.920
Hunter watches Peters face.

22:15.920 --> 22:18.920
He doesn't have the necklace.

22:18.920 --> 22:20.920
She just knows it.

22:20.920 --> 22:23.920
She looks at his computer.

22:23.920 --> 22:26.920
Is there something here?

22:26.920 --> 22:28.920
She thinks.

22:28.920 --> 22:32.920
Aparti turns to Hunter.

22:32.920 --> 22:35.920
Nothing, he says again.

22:35.920 --> 22:37.920
Hunter looks up.

22:37.920 --> 22:43.920
She thinks for a minute and walks away from Peters a little.

22:43.920 --> 22:46.920
Aparti goes with her.

22:46.920 --> 22:51.920
Peters steals things for people, says Hunter.

22:51.920 --> 22:54.920
Then they give him money.

22:54.920 --> 22:56.920
She looks at Aparti.

22:56.920 --> 23:00.920
Someone wants the money he can necklace.

23:00.920 --> 23:05.920
They ask Peters and he steals it for them.

23:05.920 --> 23:07.920
He gives them the necklace.

23:07.920 --> 23:10.920
They give him the money.

23:10.920 --> 23:13.920
She starts to speak fast now.

23:13.920 --> 23:15.920
But how much money?

23:15.920 --> 23:18.920
She asks Aparti.

23:18.920 --> 23:20.920
$100,000?

23:20.920 --> 23:23.920
$200,000?

23:23.920 --> 23:26.920
Aparti doesn't answer.

23:26.920 --> 23:29.920
No one in Rura Tonga has that much money.

23:29.920 --> 23:32.920
We know that, she says.

23:32.920 --> 23:35.920
Then she puts a hand to her head.

23:35.920 --> 23:38.920
Of course, she says,

23:38.920 --> 23:41.920
Kate Watson.

23:41.920 --> 23:43.920
She looks at Aparti.

23:43.920 --> 23:46.920
Her plane, she asks.

23:46.920 --> 23:49.920
But Aparti has his phone out.

23:49.920 --> 23:52.920
This is Inspector Aparti, he says.

23:52.920 --> 23:56.920
The plane to Los Angeles must not leave.

23:56.920 --> 23:59.920
It must not leave.

23:59.920 --> 24:04.920
Get everyone off the plane and into the airport now.

24:04.920 --> 24:07.920
Aparti puts his phone away.

24:07.920 --> 24:13.920
I'm going to speak to Kate Watson, he says to Hunter.

24:13.920 --> 24:16.920
Okay, says Hunter.

24:16.920 --> 24:21.920
And I'm going to try and find something on this computer.

24:21.920 --> 24:25.920
Aparti goes up to Peters.

24:25.920 --> 24:29.920
You come with me, he says.

24:29.920 --> 24:35.920
Chapter 7.

24:35.920 --> 24:39.920
Finding the answers.

24:39.920 --> 24:45.920
At 12 o'clock, Aparti is sitting in a room at the airport.

24:45.920 --> 24:48.920
Peters and Kate Watson are there,

24:48.920 --> 24:54.920
and two police officers are next to Watson's bags.

24:54.920 --> 24:57.920
Kate Watson is angry.

24:58.920 --> 25:02.920
I tell you, I don't know this man.

25:02.920 --> 25:07.920
And I don't know anything about a necklace, she shouts.

25:07.920 --> 25:10.920
And just look at my bags.

25:10.920 --> 25:14.920
You can't leave them like that.

25:14.920 --> 25:18.920
I'm not going to forget this, you know.

25:18.920 --> 25:20.920
Just then, the door opens.

25:20.920 --> 25:22.920
It's a police officer.

25:22.920 --> 25:25.920
He's with Maria Gomez.

25:25.920 --> 25:28.920
And he has a small bag.

25:28.920 --> 25:30.920
Excuse me, Inspector.

25:30.920 --> 25:36.920
He says, we've got this from the plane under seat 3A.

25:36.920 --> 25:40.920
Where Ms. Gomez is sitting.

25:40.920 --> 25:44.920
Everyone in the room looks at Maria Gomez.

25:44.920 --> 25:47.920
Her face goes white.

25:47.920 --> 25:53.920
The police officer opens the bag and puts something on the table.

25:53.920 --> 25:56.920
The money he can necklace.

25:56.920 --> 25:59.920
Everyone looks at it.

25:59.920 --> 26:03.920
I don't understand, says Maria Gomez.

26:03.920 --> 26:06.920
Her face now goes red.

26:06.920 --> 26:09.920
I know nothing about this.

26:09.920 --> 26:13.920
Just then, Peters gets up.

26:13.920 --> 26:17.920
Well, you have your woman, Inspector.

26:17.920 --> 26:20.920
I can go now, he says.

26:20.920 --> 26:25.920
But Hunter is by the open door with Peters' computer.

26:25.920 --> 26:28.920
Sit down, Peters, she says.

26:28.920 --> 26:31.920
You're not going anywhere.

26:31.920 --> 26:37.920
Hunter puts the computer on the table and turns it to a party.

26:37.920 --> 26:41.920
Computers are funny things, Peters, she says.

26:41.920 --> 26:48.920
It's easy to put something on a computer, but it's never easy to take it off.

26:48.920 --> 26:51.920
Let e-mail from your bank.

26:51.920 --> 26:57.920
Not easy for me to find, but very interesting.

26:57.920 --> 27:02.920
Eppity reads the e-mail and smiles.

27:02.920 --> 27:06.920
From ATM Bank, Geneva.

27:06.920 --> 27:09.920
To Wolfgang Peters.

27:09.920 --> 27:13.920
W Peters at crimco.org.

27:13.920 --> 27:16.920
ATMG, Wolfgang Peters.

27:16.920 --> 27:23.920
988-456-7543-108.

27:23.920 --> 27:26.920
Money from KW Films.

27:26.920 --> 27:31.920
$250,000.

27:31.920 --> 27:36.920
Thank you, Inspector Hunter, says Eppity.

27:36.920 --> 27:40.920
That's very good work.

27:40.920 --> 27:43.920
Hunter looks at Kate Watson.

27:43.920 --> 27:47.920
And KW Films, she says.

27:47.920 --> 27:51.920
Is that Maria Gomez films?

27:51.920 --> 27:56.920
Or is it Kate Watson films?

27:56.920 --> 27:59.920
Kate Watson looks across at Peters.

27:59.920 --> 28:03.920
Her eyes are dark and angry.

28:03.920 --> 28:07.920
You stupid man, she says.

28:07.920 --> 28:13.920
You stupid, stupid man.

28:30.920 --> 28:34.920
Here's the beginning of another book at this level.

28:34.920 --> 28:39.920
A Death in Oxford, by Richard McCandrew.

28:39.920 --> 28:42.920
Chapter 1.

28:42.920 --> 28:49.920
Friday, 26th July, 6.30 am.

28:49.920 --> 28:53.920
It's 6.30 in the morning.

28:53.920 --> 28:58.920
Inspector Frank Williams of the Oxford Police is in bed.

28:58.920 --> 29:02.920
He hears his phone and answers it.

29:02.920 --> 29:06.920
Williams, he says.

29:06.920 --> 29:09.920
It's Kate Miller, Inspector.

29:09.920 --> 29:13.920
I'm at 17B St John Street.

29:13.920 --> 29:17.920
The House of a Doctor Janet Layton.

29:17.920 --> 29:20.920
She's dead.

29:20.920 --> 29:23.920
I'm coming, says Williams.

29:23.920 --> 29:27.920
Give me 15 minutes.

29:27.920 --> 29:35.920
At 6.45, Williams walks into the front room of a tall house on St John Street.

29:35.920 --> 29:37.920
He stops.

29:37.920 --> 29:44.920
There are books and papers everywhere, and a body next to the coffee table.

29:44.920 --> 29:47.920
Sergeant Kate Miller is by the window.

29:47.920 --> 29:50.920
She's waiting for him.

29:50.920 --> 29:54.920
There's a police scientist in the room too.

29:54.920 --> 29:58.920
What's all this? asks Williams.

29:58.920 --> 30:05.920
Someone wanting money or things to sell, I think, says Miller.

30:05.920 --> 30:11.920
This is Doctor Layton's computer table, but there's no computer.

30:11.920 --> 30:15.920
And there's her bag.

30:15.920 --> 30:18.920
Williams looks down at the body.

30:18.920 --> 30:21.920
It's the body of a 50-year-old woman.

30:21.920 --> 30:27.920
Dark trousers and a white shirt with a lot of red.

30:27.920 --> 30:30.920
Miller speaks again.

30:30.920 --> 30:33.920
And there's this.

30:33.920 --> 30:40.920
In her hand is a bag, and in the bag is a knife.

30:40.920 --> 30:43.920
Oh, says Williams.

30:43.920 --> 30:47.920
He looks slowly at the room again.

30:47.920 --> 30:50.920
He looks at the Chinese dog.

30:50.920 --> 30:52.920
He turns it over.

30:52.920 --> 30:56.920
What do you think, Sergeant?

30:56.920 --> 30:58.920
He asks.

30:58.920 --> 31:03.920
Someone gets into the house to take things, she says.

31:03.920 --> 31:06.920
Doctor Layton tries to stop them.

31:06.920 --> 31:13.920
But maybe there's a knife on the table, and she stops speaking.

31:13.920 --> 31:16.920
Williams says nothing for a minute.

31:16.920 --> 31:20.920
He looks at the Chinese dog again.

31:20.920 --> 31:24.920
I don't know, says Williams.

31:24.920 --> 31:27.920
He turns to the police scientist.

31:27.920 --> 31:34.920
Jenkins, he says, can I have a photograph of this dog?

31:34.920 --> 31:38.920
Okay, Inspector, says the scientist.

31:38.920 --> 31:43.920
Williams looks at the book on the coffee table.

31:43.920 --> 31:46.920
Our beautiful world.

31:46.920 --> 31:49.920
He reads the name of the book.

31:49.920 --> 31:53.920
Photographs from all over the world.

31:53.920 --> 31:56.920
There's a receipt by the book.

31:56.920 --> 31:58.920
He looks at that.

31:58.920 --> 32:02.920
It's a new book, too, he says.

32:02.920 --> 32:08.920
Next, Williams looks at the papers on the computer table.

32:08.920 --> 32:10.920
One is a letter.

32:10.920 --> 32:12.920
He reads it.

32:12.920 --> 32:15.920
Interesting, he says.

32:15.920 --> 32:21.920
It's about Doctor Layton's will from her lawyer.

32:21.920 --> 32:24.920
I want to know about her will.

32:24.920 --> 32:27.920
Now she's dead.

32:27.920 --> 32:29.920
Who gets her money?

32:29.920 --> 32:30.920
Her husband?

32:30.920 --> 32:32.920
Children?

32:32.920 --> 32:36.920
Miller comes over and reads the letter.

32:36.920 --> 32:44.920
The lawyer's name is Elizabeth Morgan of Morgan and Free Body Lawyers, she says.

32:44.920 --> 32:47.920
We can talk to her this morning.

32:47.920 --> 32:56.920
Yes, says Williams, but first I want to see a Doctor Barbara Collins.

32:56.920 --> 33:01.920
Miller looks at Williams, but he turns to the scientist.

33:01.920 --> 33:05.920
Jenkins, can you come and see me this afternoon?

33:05.920 --> 33:09.920
Okay, Inspector, says the scientist.

33:09.920 --> 33:17.920
You can tell me all about this room then, says Williams, and about the knife.

33:17.920 --> 33:20.920
Williams turns to Miller.

33:20.920 --> 33:24.920
Okay, Sergeant, we can go.

33:24.920 --> 33:29.920
Whose Doctor Barbara Collins asks Miller?

33:29.920 --> 33:33.920
Williams and Miller are in Williams' car.

33:33.920 --> 33:37.920
They are driving up the Woodstock Road.

33:37.920 --> 33:44.920
It's a beautiful Oxford street with trees and houses to the left and the right.

33:44.920 --> 33:48.920
You're new in Oxford, I know, says Williams.

33:48.920 --> 33:52.920
But don't you read the Oxford Post?

33:52.920 --> 33:57.920
I don't have time, answers Miller.

33:57.920 --> 34:04.920
Williams turns left into French Road and stops in front of a big house.

34:04.920 --> 34:07.920
He looks at Miller and smiles.

34:07.920 --> 34:16.920
Well, a lot of people in Oxford know Doctor Collins and Doctor Layton.

